.TH hsh 1 "February 2025" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.br
[no arguments]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B hsh
program is a simple UNIX command interpreter.
It reads commands from the standard input and executes them, either in
interactive mode (reading from a terminal) or in non-interactive mode
(reading from a pipe or file).

This shell supports:
.IP \[bu]
Executing commands given with an absolute or relative path
.IP \[bu]
Passing arguments to commands
.IP \[bu]
Searching for commands in the directories listed in PATH
.IP \[bu]
The built-in commands
.B exit
and
.B env

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.PP
.EX
$ ./hsh
$ /bin/ls
$ ls -l /tmp
$ env
$ exit
.EE

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.EE

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH AUTHOR
Kevin Voka

